sec.p:
We excluded orthologous sequences from species lacking RNA‐seq data (Ca. grahami, Ch. rufifacies, and 
L. sericata
), retaining clusters with at least two remaining sequences (n = 13,370). We performed multiple‐sequence alignments with MAFFT v7.310 (Katoh and Standley 2013) and then removed gaps in the beginning and end of each alignment. We selected all clusters whose aligned sequences were at least 300 bp long and, within each selected cluster, removed all gaps, and individually excluded unaligned sequences less than 300 bp.
